  "text": "These evidences demonstrate that the three countries where the CRMS was validated are culturally divergent, which corroborates the external validity and the generalization in different contexts. Such cultural differences may explain the divergent results found in the three versions of the CRMS. It is to be noticed that diverse researches show that the cultural dimension indeed causes impact on the consumers' behavior, due to perceived quality of the service (Kuek & Voo, 2007) , intention to buy [CITATION_1] , complaint behavior [CITATION_2] , impulse of buying [CITATION_3] , mouth to mouth behavior (Lam, Lee, & Mizersk, 2009) .",
